Sweet Potato Casserole Cookies
Sweet potato cookies with brown sugar oat streusel topping
classic
Sweet, Soft, Spiced

INGREDIENTS:
2 1/4 cups all-purpose flour
3/8 cup butter
3/8 cup sweet potato puree
3/4 cup brown sugar
3/4 cup white sugar
2 eggs
1 tbsp baking soda
1 tbsp vanilla extract
Brown sugar oat streusel topping

INSTRUCTIONS:
Preheat oven to 350Â°F. Line baking sheets with parchment paper
Beat butter, sweet potato puree and sugars until smooth
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until well blended
Add flour, baking soda and salt; beat until combined
Form tablespoon-sized dough balls and place 2in apart on sheet
Top with streusel mixture
Bake just until cookies lose their shiny appearance, about 12 minutes
Let cookies cool for 10 minutes before removing. Makes 40-50 cookies